               <p>
                  <rs id="t18180401-168-viclabel953" type="occupation">MR</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180401-168-victim1222 t18180401-168-viclabel953"></join>. 
               <persName id="t18180401-168-person1223">
                  GEORGE 
                  ALEXANDER REID
               <interp inst="t18180401-168-person1223" type="surname" value="ALEXANDER REID"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180401-168-person1223" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180401-168-person1223" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was in <placeName id="t18180401-168-crimeloc954">Oxford-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18180401-168-crimeloc954" type="placeName" value="Oxford-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18180401-168-crimeloc954" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180401-168-off951 t18180401-168-crimeloc954"></join>, on the 23d of February, about two o'clock; Perkins told me I had lost my handkerchief, I immediately missed it; he said the boy was gone up the adjoining court. The prisoner was secured.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18180401-168-person1224">
                  JOHN 
                  PERKINS
               <interp inst="t18180401-168-person1224" type="surname" value="PERKINS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180401-168-person1224" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180401-168-person1224" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an apprentice to Mr. Hiscock, of North Audley-street. I saw a little boy take the handkerchief out of Mr. Reid's pocket, and give it to the prisoner, who put it into his hat - He was close to the boy - I went and told Mr. Reid. The prisoner, and another person, who was with him, went up Gee-court; they separated, and met again at the corner. Mr. Reid called out Stop thief! a man stopped the prisoner, and found the handkerchief in his hat.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18180401-168-person1225">
                  RICHARD 
                  SMITH
               <interp inst="t18180401-168-person1225" type="surname" value="SMITH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180401-168-person1225" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180401-168-person1225" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. I heard the alarm, and saw the prisoner running up Marylebone-lane; he was stopped, and the handkerchief fell out of his hat.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18180401-168-verdict955" type="verdictDescription">
